<p>
Below you can find the syllabus of my Perl 6 training class.
Trainigs based on this syllabus have been given on several occassions in places
such as Oslo, Norway in 2009; Lisbon, Portugal 2009; and in Pisa, Italy in 2010.
</p>

<p>
If you are interested in this course, please <a href="/about#contact">contact me</a>.
</p>

<h2>Length</h2>
<p>
The training course can be 1 or 2 days long. (9:00-17:00 each day.)
</p>

<h2>Syllabus</h2>
<p>
<b>Setup</b>
<ul>
<li>Setting up <a href="http://www.parrot.org/">Parrot</a>
and <a href="http://www.rakudo.org/">Rakudo</a> to be able to run Perl 6</li>
<li>Setting up <a href="http://padre.perlide.org/">Padre, the Perl IDE</a></li>
</ul>
<b>Basics</b>
<ul>
<li>Scalars</li>
<li>Basic I/O</li>
<li>Dealing with Files (I/O)</li>
<li>Control Structures (loops, conditionals)</li>
<li>Chained comparison</li>
<li>Lists and Arrays</li>
<li>Hashes</li>
<li>Subroutines, Multi dispatch subroutines, signatures</li>
<li>Junctions</li>
</ul>
<b>Advanced</b>
<ul>
<li>Regexes, Grammars and Rules</li>
<li>Classes</li>
<li>Meta operators</li>
</ul>
</p>

<h2>Course Materials</h2>
<p>
You can find the course material with extensive additional text available as
the <a href="/tutorial/">Perl 6 tutorial</a>.
</p>


